<Author>love_2_travel666
<Content>Central Location Went to Barcelona for first time for a few days early March. Found the hotel from searching on google for hotels in City Centre locations. This Hotel says it is a 4* and I believe it is. Exterior is traditional but they have ripped out the interior and made it into a boutique hotel, with lots of wooden floors and panels. The main stairs in reception are still authentic.The reception staff were very helpful and advice on where to eat and what to do was very welcome.The hotel had a special offer if booking for 3 days or more you could have a buffet breakfast for 1/2 price, which for us was 鈧? per person per day instead of 鈧?6. Well worth it, self service for everything from Tea/Coffee to full cooked breakfast. Plenty of choice of fresh fruits and the usual pastries etc. Our room was a good size. We were at the back of the hotel in a double bed, with a sitting/changing area. We overlooked the school which could be noisy at break times and early evening when playing football or basketball tournaments, however we went to Barcelona for the sights not just the hotel. The only draw back, there was no tea/coffee facilities in the room. Mini bar had a good choice at a reasonable cost, however still and sparkling water were free and replaced daily.Safe deposit box in room was also free.Bathroom suited us fine, with good size bathrobes and slippers, and everything you would need for a short break in the way of toiletries, including toothbrushes, and wet shave equipment.We used the hotel pool and jacuzzi everyday, although one day the jacuzzi was out of order as 'someone' had put in some soap!! You need to know in advance if you want to use the sauna so the reception staff can ensure it is hot enough.The hotel recommend on their website to use the aerobus from the airport. 鈧?.90 which was a good choice, it picked up outside the arrivals hall, last stop out of 3 was at Paca Catalunya, 2 blocks from the hotel, the map the hotel provide was very accurate.Barcelona is definitely on our list to re-visit and I will be booking this hotel again. 
