<Content>Perfect location for stay in Barcelona We stayed in the Atrium Palace for 3 nights in Feb 2007 and have to say it is a little gem in the centre of Barcelona. We took the train when we arrived at the airport - EUR2.50 per person one way and the train stops at the Passeig de Gracia metro station about 200 metres from the hotel. Check in was smooth and we were able to check in at 1pm when we arrived. In the room, there were lots of handy toiletries - toothbrush, razor, shampoo, shower gel, tissues, lavender hand wipes. We also got bathrobes and slippers in our hotel which you're instructed to wear down to the spa - spa is lovely, small pool, jacuzzi (which was not very hot!) and a sauna which was lovely. Towels were provided in the spa so no need to take any down with you. The rooms were great, extra pillows provided, in room safe, ironing board, limited tv channels but we didnt really watch it too much. Also view from our room was of the basement but we didnt mind, as we didnt spend all that much time in the room. A nice touch was the 2 free bottles of still and 2 free bottles of sparkling water in the room every day. Reception staff were great - we had forgotten to take a charger with us and they let us borrow one for our stay and also on one of our days there, it rained and they loaned us a large umbrella to take out with us for the day. It's so central though - on the Gran Via des Cort Catalanes, 5 mins brisk walk to Plaza Catalunya and a few mins further takes you to the top of Las ramblas.I will definitely be back to the Atrium Palace. 
