<Content>Beware The Atrium Palace is a very nice hotel. It has a great location, has beautiful rooms, and a very helpful front desk staff. That being said, one has to be very careful in Barcelona, like a lot of European cities. Barcelona is a city of theives. Don't believe me? Walk the busy city streets and look at the women at the sidewalk cafes. Every single one has their purse on their lap, directly in front of them. The reason is simple. Purse snatching is rampant. Please protect yourself with a money belt and don't don't carry anything valuable in a purse. We didn't think it would happen to us. But my wife had her had firmly on her purse and it was snatched from her in front of a dozen people. To their credit, the local people were very sympathic and offered us tremendous compassion and help in our time of need. I don't mean to demean the city of Barcelona. It's a beautiful place and I would visit it again in a hot second. Back to the Atrium Palace. We went directly back to the hotel after the purse snatching an they were very helpful in getting our credit cards stopped and so on. But, the next morning, the mini-bar guy came into our room while we were sleeping and stole 100 euros from our room! I couldn't believe it. I went immediately to the front desk to report this, but it was his word against ours. First of all, I admit to being an idiot. One should never leave money out in plain view in a hotel room. My mistake, to trust the hotel staff. The lesson here is a) Barelona is beatufiul and a very worthy place to visit, and b) expect to be stolen from at the slightest opporunity. 
