<Content>Centrally located, loved this hotel. We ( a family of 4) had a wonderful stay at the Apsis Atrium Palace(Barcelona, Spain) in Late Feb. We had 2 rooms on the front of the hotel overlooking the beautiful Boulevard. We booked our room through the hotel's own web site and got the best rates. We booked early and received a discount for staying over 3 nights. By booking thru the hotel yourself, there are no booking fees and you can cancel up to two days before with no penalty. Also, you don't pay anything until you check out. This 4 star hotel was no more expensive than many of the 3 stars I looked at. As per previous posts, the room is a little warm, but when we opened the Balcony doors, we cooled off the room and it was great. The staff was marvelous and attentive. They offered help with directions, luggage, etc. There are 2 (easy to use)computers with free internet access in the second floor business center. There was free water/juice in the mini bar as advertised. Also, there were lots of free toiletries in the room including a toothbrush/paste, razor, and all the usuals, etc. (nice touch) The hotel is clean. This hotel is very centrally located to all Barcelona attractions in a safe area. It's just two blocks to Placa Catalunya (transportation hub)and a few blocks to El Corte Ingles dept store.(has full supermarket in basement)There is also a citibank 2 blocks away.Las Ramblas was a 5 min walk. The hotel is near many of the Gaudi sites. We took the hop on/hop off bus which was a great way to get acclimated to Barcelona and hopped off at the sites that were harder to get to. We didn't have the hotel breakfast, it was pricey, but found lots of inexpensive cafes nearby to eat in.We found a superb restaurant that just opened next door to the hotel Patagonia Beef and Wine It's an argentinian steak house. The service was as great as the food and freshly made sangria. We ate there 2 out of our 5 nights. It was that good. All in all, Apsis Atrium Hotel is a centrally located, safe, clean hotel with lots of extras. I highly recommend it and will stay there again when I return to Barcelona. 
