<Content>My New Favorite Hotel in Barcelona I'm glad I took a chance and stayed at this hotel. I was attending a conference at the Ritz but my company would have freaked if I turned in an expense report from there - besides, the Ritz is a little moldy at this point (except for the bar - awesome but incredibly expensive). Atrium Palace staff were uniformly well trained, very helpful/friendly without being smarmy. Room was spotless, completely quiet (and I had a room facing the school playground), very hip in its design (from the Grohe fixtures to the floor-to-ceiling marble in the bathroom), the wood floors (OK they're Pergo, but that keeps it clean and it still looks great), very comfortable Queen bed with a super-thick fleece blanket and down duvet, crisp new sheets, very useful desk for getting work done, and high speed Internet (ignore the warnings from the Concierge - it's not that expensive).Location was perfect - 5 minute walk to the Gothic Quarter, 1 minute to the Ritz bar, opens onto the Gran Via for strolling or jogging, 2 minutes from Gracia for shopping, 1 block from neighborhood bars and patisseries for breakfast or a snacks.The hotel Restaurant/Cafe/Bar was clean, hip, great staff, very convenient, very good food and drinks. Will I stay here again - absolutely!One thought regarding the vacationer from Dublin who was bothered by the distant muffled sound of children - you need more than a vacation. And, if the noise bothers you, just close the window, or get out of bed by 8:30 in the morning - it's Barcelona, what are you doing hiding out in your room? 
