<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Break Some of the comments I have read on here I agree with others I dont. First the hotel staff and the accomodation were excellent staff very friendly and always helpful. Rooms are spotless and are cleaned to a very high standard everyday. Breakfast I would agree is a little on the expensive side at 15 Euros each. Yes there is plenty and its fine, we eat there once and then tried a small down the road and had coffee and rolls for 4.5 euros each, quite a bit of differance. This kind of holiday you need to have a rest now and again and so more coffee and cakes at about 12.00 go down pretty well! The coach from the airport drops you off close to the hotel, they say its 450 metres but in my opinion its more like 800. Which is fine as long as you go in the right direction when you get off the coach! Look down the road you will see a massive roundabout you need to turn RIGHT as you look at it. The hotel is then on the other side of this road its just past the RITZ hotel. If you ask directions ask for the RITZ as it is more well known not many taxi drivers seemed to know it, probably because it has only recently re-opened. We were also at the back of the hotel on the top floor (the rooms on the top floor are smaller but they have a balcony instead, quite large and its really sunny in the morning) Yes it does overlook a large courtyard where they play handball, basketball etc and there is a school with a playground which is amazingly on a rooftop! But the noise didnt bother us at all. The playtimes are during the day, when you are out, the sport goes on until 9.00 at night, also out!!! So the only time we heard it was about 6.00 in the evening when we came back to shower and change. Another tip is the drinks in the mini bar in the rooms are pretty cheap we had two small bottles of wine a brandy and a vodka for 8 euros, and all the soft non fizzy drinks are free. The hotel bar is very cheap although its not that exciting! There is a safe in the rooms (free of charge) and they are excellent suggest you use that, also ironing facilities. The bathroom and shower facilities are top class. Also they have 2 internet terminals in a quiet room (with a free coffee machine!) and you can use the internet for free, its on broadband and works very well. There are TV's in the room with lots of pay per view stuff, the free channels are VERY boring, with only CNN, BBC WORLD NEWS and EUROSPORT that are in English. You have to visit the rambles during the evening as a visit would not be a visit without going there, but the resturants in this area are pretty poor, and they will rip you off ALWAYS check your bill. If you go out of the area you will find better, here is a comparsion one vodka and orange and a beer in two irish bars on the rambles was 12 euros and 14 euros! Two Spanish brandy and coke and three glasses of white wine in a sidestreet near the hotel was 9 euros! How do you work that out! Tip for a resturant and it is EXCELLENT was El Rodizio its 403 Consell de Cent and that road is out of the hotel staight across the road go up two blocks and turn right, its about 500 yards. All you can eat for 12 Euros each, but the food is per excellence! The meat is cooked on skewers and is perfect. All in all I would use the hotel again it is very good indeed, hope some of these tips helps you enjoy your stay. 
